reviews.review: I liked the movie a very conservative approach to Star Wars because of the last movie but over all a very effective piece. Characters were developed well and had sufficient wrap up to call it a final. Felt rushed and felt like 3 movies into 1, not the fault of this move merely the fault of 8 in my opinion. Further plot development needed in 8 to really give a finally the final goodbye it needed in 9. Snoke being killed was a major flaw in the last Jedi and thus Palatine needs to fill the roll which should have been filled by Snoke.

It really is not the end this saga deserves. It's visually beautiful, but hollow and messy. This film should have deserved 2 more films or two more years to be well done. An arguably forgettable movie.

Visually spectacular. Emotive scenes that brought a tear to my eye, with plenty of plot twists and surprises. There is a lot crammed into the film and I feel like some of this could and should have been fleshed out in TLJ. BUT I suppose you feel like you're going along on the ride as a result. There wasn't a scene that I didn't enjoy unlike TLJ and so I look forward to seeing this again. Well done JJ

a great end for the best saga, Kylo Ren is one of the best characters in this movie, and Rey is the best in this new trilogy.
the return of Palpatine should have been earlier, maybe in the last Jedi, but his character was totally needed (but we need an explanation in tv/movie/comic... sth)
The legends are canon. Fuck this trilogy.
Its a perfect conclusion for an era. Trust me, its so much better than episode VII.

Whilst not a perfect film, it does a great job of wrapping up what some people might have thought was left unresolved from the end of the last installment, and still manages to provide enough fan service and action set pieces to keep both long time fans and casual movie-goers entertained. True fans of Star Wars that can see past the out-of-touch critics will likely find things to both enjoy and hate, but this will just add to the hours of debating us Star Wars fanboys love to have with ourselves. Definitely worth a watch.
